The course introduces the basics of corpus linguistics, gives an overview of the main concepts and discusses current issues in the field. It will also focus on the development of practical skills in the analysis of Estonian language corpora in order to answer (mainly linguistic) research questions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the basics of contemporary corpus linguistics, its resources and tools, and to develop students' skills in working independently with large text collections of the Estonian language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, the student - knows the basic concepts of corpus linguistics, - knows the main branches and applications of corpus linguistics, - is familiar with the main Estonian language corpora,  - is able to perform queries through the interfaces of corpora, - is able to use corpus source files,  - is able to use existing applications for compiling their own corpus, - is able to process query results, - is able to select the appropriate data and tools for specific research questions.
